      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Leafs",
        "body": "The Maple Leafs' season ended not with a bang but a whimper - a seven-game losing streak that capsized what little remained of their playoff hopes. With a 32-36-14 record and just 78 points, Toronto finished eighth in the Atlantic Division, 31 games behind the pace-setters, their 15th seed in the East a damning indictment of a season that never found its footing. <strong>The collapse was total and unforgiving, a reminder that depth and consistency matter far more than star power when March turns to April.</strong> Now comes the reckoning. The front office faces hard questions about roster construction, coaching philosophy, and whether the current core can be salvaged or must be dismantled. Free agency looms. The draft lottery awaits. The Leafs' brass must decide whether to retool around their established veterans or begin the painful work of a genuine rebuild. <strong>Watch the next two weeks closely - the decisions made in boardrooms and during exit meetings will determine whether 2026 becomes a turning point or merely another chapter in a franchise defined by unfulfilled promise.</strong>",
        "updated": "Updated May 5, 2026"
      },
